cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper proposes novel paradigms for evaluating neural network explanations in NLP, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of Long Short Term Memory networks (LSTMs) and convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computer Vision (cs.CV), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Therefore, these are the five most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
